fragment_downloaded_cb({"url": "gtkwidget.html#gtk_widget_queue_allocate", "fragment": "Gtk.Widget.queue_allocate \ngtk_widget_queue_allocate \nGtk.prototype.queue_allocate \nThis function is only for use in widget implementations. \nFlags the widget for a rerun of the GtkWidgetClass size_allocate function. Use this function instead of Gtk.Widget.queue_resize when the widget s size request didn t change but it wants to reposition its contents. \nAn example user of this function is Gtk.Widget.set_halign. \nParameters \na Gtk.Widget \nSince \nThis function is only for use in widget implementations. \nFlags the widget for a rerun of the GtkWidgetClass size_allocate function. Use this function instead of gtk_widget_queue_resize when the widget s size request didn t change but it wants to reposition its contents. \nAn example user of this function is gtk_widget_set_halign. \nParameters \na GtkWidget \nSince \nThis function is only for use in widget implementations. \nFlags the widget for a rerun of the GtkWidgetClass size_allocate function. Use this function instead of Gtk.prototype.queue_resize when the widget s size request didn t change but it wants to reposition its contents. \nAn example user of this function is Gtk.prototype.set_halign. \nParameters \na Gtk.Widget \nSince \n"});